name: without_glottocode [mirniny, variety near eucla, not subgroup]

two message sticks. a: with burnt designs in yellow. b: with incised designs, into which red paint is rubbed. the exact meaning of these sticks is not understood but they sometimes bear signs corresponding to totemic features of the route followed in transporting them.
see remarks in notes for more info re the 2nd stick.
ramm online catalogue: "this is a message stick, incised with designs that communicate a message. whole etched with diamond pattern"
